<p>GUILT</p>
<p>culpa refers to guilt as the state of one who as a rational being is responsible fro an offense of any kind.</p>
<p>noxia is the state of one who has caused an offense for which he is not necessarily criminally responsible.</p>
<p>vitium refers to an action or even a qujality in aperson which is taken to deserve censure, and the word may even refer to an undeserved defect.</p>
<p/>
<p>GUILTY</p>
<p>nocens indicates plain guilt without any judgment on character.</p>
<p>noxius and the poetic nocuus refer to the personal character of someone who is prone to incur guilt.</p>
